               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540918-name-341" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-341" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-341" type="surname" value="DENNIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-341" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN DENNIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Thomas Dennis, and mother of the prisoner—we live in Seacoal—lane, Farringdon—street. On Wednesday, 12th Sept., I had five half sovereigns and 35<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in silver, &amp;c., in the tea chest, in my bed-room—I saw the silver on Saturday—on Tuesday I missed the money, at a quarter past 8 o'clock—the lad was living at home—he went out after 7 o'clock—he came in again—I saw him coming from the bedroom—he said he only came to brush his hair—I found the money was gone—I said, "What have you done with the money?"—he first denied, then said he had but 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18540918-name-342" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-342" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-342" type="surname" value="HARRINGTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18540918-name-342" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN HARRINGTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, L</hi> 32). On Tuesday, the 12th, I was at the theatre—I took Dennis into custody—he came quietly—I told him his mother charged him with stealing 5<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.—he pointed a pistol at my head—I threw him down—he pointed another with his other hand—he said after he had only taken 30<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. of the money, and had spent them all—he said he had bought the pistols to shoot his father—they were loaded, fully cocked and capped.</p>
